This does not save money, okay?

00:47:03.960 --> 00:47:07.830
Now, it might cure
diseases more quickly.

00:47:07.830 --> 00:47:09.410
Technology does not save money

00:47:09.410 --> 00:47:12.900
at research universities,
net, net, net, net, net.

00:47:12.900 --> 00:47:19.440
So the biggest impact of
technology in my view,

00:47:19.440 --> 00:47:22.860 position:56%
and this is where I'll close on this
and segue to my final punchline.

00:47:22.860 --> 00:47:29.360
The biggest impact is, frankly,
when it's rarely mentioned.

00:47:29.360 --> 00:47:32.470
I think everything from the mooks

00:47:32.470 --> 00:47:35.880
to something called the
University of the People.

00:47:35.880 --> 00:47:38.780
Now I'm Chairman of the Board
at the University of the People.

00:47:38.780 --> 00:47:41.270
I've been Chairman for seven years.

00:47:41.270 --> 00:47:43.530 position:56%
What's the University of the People?

00:47:43.530 --> 00:47:46.450
Well, if you're a high school
graduate, you're fluent in English,

00:47:46.450 --> 00:47:50.350
you have access to the Internet,
and you are abjectly poor,

00:47:50.350 --> 00:47:52.240
you're automatically admitted.

00:47:52.240 --> 00:47:56.070
Welcome aboard, no matter
where you are in the world.

00:47:56.070 --> 00:47:58.810
And you'll get an accredited
in the United States,

00:47:58.810 --> 00:48:03.390
accredited, free college education.

00:48:03.390 --> 00:48:07.640
Here it is.

00:48:07.640 --> 00:48:10.070
All open source materials.

00:48:10.070 --> 00:48:12.300
You sign up for courses.

00:48:12.300 --> 00:48:17.360 position:56%
There are volunteer professors that
have made up the curriculum and work

00:48:17.360 --> 00:48:21.770
with the 32 students in the class
that do peer-peer learning largely.

00:48:21.770 --> 00:48:24.780
