01:13:44.510 --> 01:13:46.150
You're living it.

01:13:46.150 --> 01:13:51.050
Go home and watch <i>Sports Center</i>
tonight [laughter], okay?

01:13:51.050 --> 01:13:52.910
And see what we've done.

01:13:52.910 --> 01:13:57.600
But what it is, what
it is, you understand,

01:13:57.600 --> 01:14:02.600
that we may be witnessing is
the death of thought, right?

01:14:02.600 --> 01:14:05.850
I mean, if we just
continue to devalue thought

01:14:05.850 --> 01:14:09.870
and put aside whether it's good
or bad for research universities.

01:14:09.870 --> 01:14:11.170
It's obviously bad.

01:14:11.170 --> 01:14:12.540
But it's not good for society.

01:14:12.540 --> 01:14:13.840
It's not good.

01:14:13.840 --> 01:14:15.700
You know, we were put on
Earth as homosapiends, right?

01:14:15.700 --> 01:14:21.280
I mean, it's -- so then you see

01:14:21.280 --> 01:14:24.330
that the university can be
an antidote to this, right?

01:14:24.330 --> 01:14:25.630
And it's quixotic.

01:14:25.630 --> 01:14:29.310
But it can be an antidote to it.

01:14:29.310 --> 01:14:34.330
Then you move to globalization and,
again, it's an unavoidable thing.

01:14:34.330 --> 01:14:39.190
I mean, you know, the
phenomena that are working

01:14:39.190 --> 01:14:44.630
out are just what [inaudible] de
Jardin spoke about in the 1940's.

01:14:44.630 --> 01:14:47.390
So the world is coming together.

01:14:47.390 --> 01:14:50.660
Now are we going to come
together and cause a combustion,

01:14:50.660 --> 01:14:53.090 position:56%
or are we going to come together and
create a community of communities?

01:14:53.090 --> 01:14:55.180
Again, this is a very big question.

01:14:55.180 --> 01:14:59.630
Again, higher education has
a key role to play in it.

01:14:59.630 --> 01:15:05.960
And then you get to technology
and technology is not the enemy

01:15:05.960 --> 01:15:07.310
of what we're trying to do here.

01:15:07.310 --> 01:15:09.440
It's -- I don't worry
about it being disruptive.

01:15:09.440 --> 01:15:12.470
It's not going to disrupt.

01:15:12.470 --> 01:15:19.990
It's going to change many
different parts of the orchestra.

01:15:19.990 --> 01:15:22.460
And if we use it right, it will
democratize higher education

01:15:22.460 --> 01:15:25.180
as long as we have ladders up.

01:15:25.180 --> 01:15:30.560 position:56%
Okay? But it can't be used to stamp
other people's kids with a BA degree

01:15:30.560 --> 01:15:33.200
and declare a political victory.

01:15:33.200 --> 01:15:35.990
That's the danger, you see.

01:15:35.990 --> 01:15:37.290
That's the danger.

01:15:37.290 --> 01:15:39.000
It's that it runs down the value.

01:15:39.000 --> 01:15:43.160
And, you know, oh, look, our
college graduation rates are up.

01:15:43.160 --> 01:15:47.310
And then the final element that I
meant is meant to tie it together.

01:15:47.310 --> 01:15:49.570
And this is, John, the
point that you're making.

01:15:49.570 --> 01:15:51.800
And I tie it back positively
to the point

01:15:51.800 --> 01:15:56.450
that was made out of the Caribbean.

01:15:56.450 --> 01:15:58.130
For me, it's a moral issue.

01:15:58.130 --> 01:16:01.440
For the, the humanitarian
argument is enough.

01:16:01.440 --> 01:16:04.070
You cannot waste a
mind that's out there.

01:16:04.070 --> 01:16:06.650
And I've lived it because I
teach these kids in Abu Dhabi.

01:16:06.650 --> 01:16:09.660
And I'm telling you it's
an amazing thing to see.

01:16:09.660 --> 01:16:12.750
And they -- and to know that
the Moosebah's and the Teyho's

01:16:12.750 --> 01:16:16.970
and the others would
have had nothing

01:16:16.970 --> 01:16:18.270
because they never
would have been found

01:16:18.270 --> 01:16:19.930
and they never would have
known it made a difference.

01:16:19.930 --> 01:16:25.510
And then to see the Syrian kids and
they know it makes a difference.

01:16:25.510 --> 01:16:29.240
So it's not enough.

01:16:29.240 --> 01:16:32.320
This is where the flavor of
Rawlsianism has to come in.

01:16:32.320 --> 01:16:35.040
And it was my last, my kind of
punchline that pulls it together.

01:16:35.040 --> 01:16:39.670
As we think about the --
elevating civic discourse

01:16:39.670 --> 01:16:44.160 position:56%
and embracing globalization and
utilizing technology to the maximum,

01:16:44.160 --> 01:16:48.470
it's only going to work if
we generalize it in a way

01:16:48.470 --> 01:16:50.800
that we don't know where, you know,

01:16:50.800 --> 01:16:55.130
in the Rawls Table
we're sitting, you know?

01:16:55.130 --> 01:16:57.810
And it works for everybody
at the table.

01:16:57.810 --> 01:17:05.600
And that requires a fairly
massive investment of resources

01:17:05.600 --> 01:17:09.260
because the education that we want
at those best schools, by the way,

01:17:09.260 --> 01:17:13.600
is -- and I'll just close
by recommending a book --

01:17:13.600 --> 01:17:17.050
<i>Why Does College Cost So Much </i>?

01:17:17.050 --> 01:17:19.950
Okay? <i>Why Does College
Cost So Much </i>?

01:17:19.950 --> 01:17:23.070
And it's because in a
well-functioning economy,

01:17:23.070 --> 01:17:27.150
a high-talent service industry goes
up more rapidly than inflation.

01:17:27.150 --> 01:17:28.670
So then the only question
becomes, okay,

01:17:28.670 --> 01:17:31.490
if it's the cost that's
going up, what's the subsidy?

01:17:31.490 --> 01:17:34.270 position:56%
And cost minus subsidy equals price.

01:17:34.270 --> 01:17:37.030
And it doesn't require a
rocket scientist to figure

01:17:37.030 --> 01:17:40.120
out if you withdraw subsidy
and cost is going up,

01:17:40.120 --> 01:17:41.970
price is going to go up.

01:17:41.970 --> 01:17:44.910
Or quality is going to go down.

01:17:44.910 --> 01:17:46.600
So we, you know, we got
to get out of this kind

01:17:46.600 --> 01:17:49.770
of very simple minded
debate that, you know --

01:17:49.770 --> 01:17:52.680
and it all works synergistically
to me because that's

01:17:52.680 --> 01:17:56.570
when the demagogue can say to
those who are allergic to nuance

01:17:56.570 --> 01:17:59.410
and complexity, your
costs are going up.

01:17:59.410 --> 01:18:00.770
So the solution is what?

01:18:00.770 --> 01:18:04.000
Give everybody -- freeze tuition.

01:18:04.000 --> 01:18:05.350
Okay, freeze tuition.

01:18:05.350 --> 01:18:09.040
I'll go on record right now and
say that is a stupid policy.

01:18:09.040 --> 01:18:11.700
Freezing tuition gives Donald Trump

01:18:11.700 --> 01:18:15.440
and William Gates's
children scholarships.

01:18:15.440 --> 01:18:17.160
Okay? It doesn't make sense.

01:18:17.160 --> 01:18:20.900 position:56%
But it's hard to -- there will be
another talk to explain that to you.

01:18:20.900 --> 01:18:23.140
But I'm telling you, that's
not the good social policy.

01:18:23.140 --> 01:18:24.630
And we got to get to
ourselves to a point

01:18:24.630 --> 01:18:27.590
where these four things are
working together positively.

01:18:27.590 --> 01:18:29.480
And then we can have a
world that we're proud of.

01:18:29.480 --> 01:18:31.720
It's not going to happen
in my lifetime,

01:18:31.720 --> 01:18:33.700
but it will happen
in Jane's, I'm sure.

01:18:33.700 --> 01:18:35.000
All right.

